100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 12, 1925, tensions escalated in the Middle East as British forces clashed with Arab nationalists in Palestine, raising concerns over stability in the region. In Europe, the League of Nations convened to address the ongoing economic crisis affecting member states. Meanwhile, the United States continued to grapple with Prohibition, as illegal speakeasies thrived amid ongoing debates over the 18th Amendment.
